Value.value: You take the magical pot with you.
The pottery in this room was crafted by a skilled hand. Numerous inscriptions seem to pay a deep homage to the land and what appear to be prominent elementals of the island.
Predating the pottery wheel, pottery of this type was created by piling ropes of clay and smoothing with a stone. Pots this fine evidently took a very practiced hand.
This place is decorated with a bunch of pots. You have no idea if they have any significance, however.
This expertly woven, but half-finished piece appears to depict a great reverence to some form of sky deity.
Exhibiting a mastery over weaving, this fabric appears to be woven of cotten, plant fibers, and even feathers. The subject appears to be religious of some kind.
The geometric patterns of this half-finished piece are quite appealing.

Value.value: You manage to decipher enough of the language to determine that the final days of this civilization were marked by paranoia, panic, and ritual sacrifice. The signs and descriptions seem to indicate a demon's handiwork.
These tablets seem to bear a language along with hieroglyphs. You can't really make heads or tails of them.

You manage to decipher enough of the hieroglyphics to determine that the final days of this civilization were marked by a great deal of trauma. A dark cloud with evil eyes seems to hang over the heads of the people depicted.
